Conflict checking shall require determining whether there were any:
changes in the controlling ownership interests over the entity; · changes in any controlling interests held by the entity; · new listings in the group; · any known change in service providers that may impact independence; or · changes in classification of the entity as public interest.
Any such changes will require reconsideration of the firm’s conflict checking procedures.
CustomField.label: Conflicting checking
